## Survey Builder System

### Overview
The survey builder uses a drag-and-drop interface with real-time question management. It follows a two-step workflow.

### Architecture

#### Step 1: Survey Metadata
**Purpose**: Collect basic survey information before adding questions.

**Fields**:
- Title (required)
- Description
- Time Limit (optional, in minutes)
- Due Date (optional)
- Status (Draft/Published/Closed)
- Assigned Sections (at least one required)

**Flow**:
```javascript
1. User fills metadata form
2. saveSurveyMetadata() validates input
3. AJAX POST to /surveys/save/
4. Server creates/updates Survey object (status='draft', no questions)
5. Returns survey_id
6. UI switches to questions builder
```

---

#### Step 2: Questions Builder

##### Drag-and-Drop Interface

**Left Sidebar (Element Palette)**:
```html
<div class="element-palette">
  <div class="element-item" draggable="true" data-type="multiple_choice">
    Multiple Choice
  </div>
  <div class="element-item" draggable="true" data-type="true_false">
    True/False
  </div>
  <!-- etc -->
</div>
```

**Canvas (Drop Zone)**:
```html
<div class="drop-zone" id="dropZone">
  <div id="questionsContainer">
    <!-- Question cards appear here -->
  </div>
</div>
```

##### Drag-and-Drop Implementation

**HTML5 Drag API**:
```javascript
// Setup draggable elements
elementItems.forEach(item => {
  item.addEventListener('dragstart', (e) => {
    draggedElement = e.target.dataset.type;  // Store question type
    e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = 'copy';
    e.target.style.opacity = '0.5';  // Visual feedback
  });
});

// Handle drop on canvas
dropZone.addEventListener('drop', (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  if (draggedElement) {
    addQuestion(draggedElement);  // Create question card
  }
});
```

**Visual Feedback**:
- Element becomes semi-transparent while dragging
- Drop zone border turns green (`drag-over` class)
- Smooth slide-in animation when card is added

---

##### Question Card Structure

Each question type has a specific card structure:

**Multiple Choice**:
```html
<div class="question-card" data-type="multiple_choice">
  <div class="question-header">
    <i class="drag-handle"></i>  <!-- For reordering -->
    <span class="badge">Multiple Choice</span>
  </div>
  <input type="text" class="question-text">
  <input type="number" class="question-points">

  <!-- Options container -->
  <div class="options-container">
    <div class="option-item">
      <input type="radio" name="correct">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Option 1">
      <button onclick="removeOption()">×</button>
    </div>
  </div>
  <button onclick="addOption()">+ Add Option</button>
</div>
```

**Dynamic Options**:
```javascript
function addOption(questionId) {
  const container = document.getElementById(`options-${questionId}`);
  const optionCount = container.children.length + 1;
  const optionHtml = `
    <div class="option-item">
      <input type="radio" name="correct-${questionId}">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Option ${optionCount}">
      <button onclick="removeOption(this)">×</button>
    </div>
  `;
  container.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', optionHtml);
}
```

---

##### Question Reordering

**Drag-to-Reorder**:
```javascript
function makeQuestionDraggable(questionCard) {
  questionCard.draggable = true;

  questionCard.addEventListener('dragstart', (e) => {
    draggedQuestionCard = questionCard;
    questionCard.classList.add('dragging');  // Semi-transparent
  });

  questionCard.addEventListener('dragover', (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const afterElement = getDragAfterElement(container, e.clientY);

    if (afterElement == null) {
      container.appendChild(draggedQuestionCard);  // Move to end
    } else {
      container.insertBefore(draggedQuestionCard, afterElement);  // Insert before
    }
  });
}

// Determine insertion point based on mouse Y position
function getDragAfterElement(container, y) {
  const draggableElements = [...container.querySelectorAll('.question-card:not(.dragging)')];

  return draggableElements.reduce((closest, child) => {
    const box = child.getBoundingClientRect();
    const offset = y - box.top - box.height / 2;

    if (offset < 0 && offset > closest.offset) {
      return { offset: offset, element: child };
    } else {
      return closest;
    }
  }, { offset: Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY }).element;
}
```

---

##### Saving Questions

**Data Collection**:
```javascript
function saveQuestions() {
  const questionCards = document.querySelectorAll('.question-card');
  const questionsData = [];

  questionCards.forEach((card, index) => {
    const type = card.dataset.type;
    const questionData = {
      type: type,
      text: card.querySelector('.question-text').value,
      points: parseInt(card.querySelector('.question-points').value),
      required: card.querySelector('.question-required').checked,
      order: index  // Order based on position in DOM
    };

    // Type-specific data
    if (type === 'multiple_choice') {
      questionData.options = [];
      card.querySelectorAll('.option-item').forEach(item => {
        const text = item.querySelector('input[type="text"]').value;
        const isCorrect = item.querySelector('input[type="radio"]').checked;
        questionData.options.push({ text, is_correct: isCorrect });
      });
    }

    questionsData.push(questionData);
  });

  // Send to server
  const surveyData = {
    survey_id: currentSurveyId,
    questions: questionsData,
    // ... other metadata
  };

  fetch('/surveys/save/', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify(surveyData)
  });
}
```

**Server-Side Processing** (views.py):
```python
@login_required
@require_http_methods(["POST"])
def save_survey(request):
    data = json.loads(request.body)
    survey_id = data.get('survey_id')

    with transaction.atomic():
        # Create/update survey
        if survey_id:
            survey = Survey.objects.get(id=survey_id)
        else:
            survey = Survey(teacher=request.user)

        survey.title = data['title']
        survey.status = data['status']
        survey.save()

        # Assign sections
        survey.sections.set(Section.objects.filter(id__in=data['sections']))

        # Delete old questions (if editing)
        survey.questions.all().delete()

        # Create new questions
        for idx, q_data in enumerate(data['questions']):
            question = Question.objects.create(
                survey=survey,
                question_type=q_data['type'],
                question_text=q_data['text'],
                points=q_data['points'],
                order=idx
            )

            # Create type-specific answer data
            if q_data['type'] == 'multiple_choice':
                for opt_idx, option in enumerate(q_data['options']):
                    MultipleChoiceOption.objects.create(
                        question=question,
                        option_text=option['text'],
                        is_correct=option['is_correct'],
                        order=opt_idx
                    )

            elif q_data['type'] == 'true_false':
                TrueFalseAnswer.objects.create(
                    question=question,
                    is_true=q_data['correct_answer']
                )

            elif q_data['type'] == 'enumeration':
                for ans_idx, answer in enumerate(q_data['answers']):
                    EnumerationAnswer.objects.create(
                        question=question,
                        answer_text=answer,
                        order=ans_idx
                    )

        # Calculate total points
        survey.calculate_total_points()

        return JsonResponse({'success': True, 'survey_id': survey.id})
```

---

### Question Types Implementation

#### 1. Multiple Choice
**UI**:
- Text input for question
- Multiple option inputs
- Radio buttons to mark correct answer
- Add/remove option buttons

**Validation**:
- At least 2 options required
- Exactly one option must be marked correct

#### 2. True/False
**UI**:
- Text input for question
- Dropdown: True or False

**Storage**:
- Creates a `TrueFalseAnswer` with `is_true` boolean

#### 3. Enumeration
**UI**:
- Text input for question
- Multiple text inputs for correct answers
- Add/remove answer buttons

**Validation**:
- At least one answer required

#### 4. Essay
**UI**:
- Text input for question
- Optional max character limit

**Storage**:
- No answer key stored (manual grading required)

